9) Create "Cost per claim & YoY by Month" Chart. 16

Now it's time to create the Charts, These are the steps to follow.

STEP 1: Order column By another column.

  1. Select "WeekDayName" Column 
  2. Click on a button named " Sort By Column" on the ribbon
  3.  Select "WeekDay"



STEP 2:  Create "Cost per claim & YoY by Month" Chart.

  1. Double click on the  "Line And Stacked column Chart" On the visualization bar.
  2. Chart visual will display on the report.
  3. Drag an drop the "Month" column from the Calendar on the Shared axis.
  4. Drag an drop the "WeekDaysName" column from the Calendar on the Shared axis bellow month.
  5. Drag an drop the ".Cost Per Claim" column from the TSA Claim on the Column Values.
  6. Drag an drop the ".YOY" column from the TSA Claim on the Line Values.
  7. Drag an drop the ".# of Claims" column from the TSA Claim on the Tooltips.
  8. You should see a chart like this.



STEP 2: Configure the "Cost per claim & YoY by Month" Visual

Part 1:

  1. Click on the Format icon
  2. Fix the  Card  Size:     X Position: 252     Y position: 84         Weight : 795                    Height: 274.
  3. Fix The Legend :    Position: Top Center      Color:  Black         Style line and markers .
  4. Fix  X axis :      Turn of Title.
  5. Fix Y axis : Color: black     Font: Arial Black    Title: off      Show secondary: On       Align Zero: on    Color :  6B007B       Font; Arial Black.
  6. Fix Data Color:   YOY Color:  A666B0          Default Color:  Click "Fx" button   Than follow picture bellow:




PART 2:

  1. Turn On the data Label :     color : 6B007B        Font: Arial Black        Background: Off                                                                            Customize series: ON        color: Black    Value decimal place : 0 .
  2. Fix shapes:  Area Shades: ON        Stroke width: 1     Show marker : ON     Marker color:  F5C4AF .
  3. Turn title on, and type: "Cost per claim & YoY by Month" .
  4. Turn on the border color :    Color  light grey     
  5. This how you chart will look like.
